Could you please keep an eye on this patch?&lt;br/&gt;
Thank you!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80823" author="askulysh" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 10:55:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch: &lt;a href=&quot;http://review.whamcloud.com/9866&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://review.whamcloud.com/9866&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="80822" author="askulysh" created="Wed, 2 Apr 2014 10:48:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The bug was caused by race between truncate &amp;amp; fsync. The problem is in osc_extent_wait().&lt;br/&gt;
There are 2 flags used for changing state : oe_trunc_pending and oe_urgent.&lt;br/&gt;
osc_cache_truncate_start() waits for all oe_urgent extents written.&lt;br/&gt;
But osc_extent_wait() doesn&apos;t takes into account oe_trunc_pending when sets oe_urgent.&lt;br/&gt;
The race arises after osc_object_unlock().&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
